--- !u!114 &5737807820702109180
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 7423393426570147508}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 1cc1efdd208710140ac043d4c3396144, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::EndingManager
  endingPanel: {fileID: 2470809400837296545}
  endingBodyText: {fileID: 2965939674979376909}
  endingTitleText: {fileID: 7909029684450912712}
  returnToMenuBtn: {fileID: 7039687505829282073}
  proMartianTitle: The Truth Teller
  proMartianBody: 'Your work arrives on Earth, with very little concern. As time
    goes on, and as you learn more, so does the public. The public starts to question
    what the narrative they''ve been given all this time, and slowly, pressure builds
    up.


    Just like all news, the public quickly forgets, and they start caring
    less and less about your writing.


    You remain on Mars, telling the stories
    as they are.


    Nothing ever comes of your writing.'
  proHumanTitle: Voice of Earth
  proHumanBody: 'Your work arrives on Earth, the public devouring your content. Outrage
    ensues, with the public urging officials to get involved more on Mars and with
    people praising what it means to be human.


    As time goes on, Mars becomes
    a resource.


    You remain on Mars, telling narratives the way you want.


    You
    become a micro-celebrity, endorsed for telling the truth and speaking your mind.'
  proSelfTitle: The Opportunist
  proSelfBody: 'Your work arrives on Earth, and major investors aren''t impressed.
    They have known for quite some time that Mars isn''t what you make it out to
    be. Fortunately for you, the normal citizen doesn''t, so some investments trickle
    in.


    As time goes on, you make some decent money, making a small empire
    on Mars.


    You remain on Mars, attempting to get more investments.


    As
    time goes on, and as your promises start to fail, you slowly lose everything.'
  secretTitle: Everything Is A Lie
  secretBody: 'Your work arrives on Earth, with lots of concern at first. As time
    goes on, and as you learn more, so does the public. The public starts to question
    what the narrative they''ve been given all this time, and slowly, pressure builds
    up. They are outraged, and demand answers.


    Just like all news, the topic
    gets covered up, and the public slowly loses interest. But something is different
    this time. The public doesn''t completely forget, and they start a movement,
    demanding answers.


    You remain on Mars, trying to uncover the truth, where
    you unfortunately meet your end.


    Your journalism, after many years, finally
    exposes some of what happens on Mars.'
